Here is an algorithm to find the maximum value in an array of numbers:

1. Initialize the first element of the array as the maximum value.
2. Loop through the rest of the array, comparing each element with the current maximum value.
3. If the current element is greater than the current maximum value, update the maximum value with the current element.
4. Continue looping through the array until all elements have been checked.
5. Return the maximum value.

Pseudocode:

```
function findMaxValue(array) {
    let maxValue = array[0];
    for (let i = 1; i < array.length; i++) {
        if (array[i] > maxValue) {
            maxValue = array[i];
        }
    }
    return maxValue;
}
```
